
  Name:  strxfrm
  
  #include <string.h>
  size_t strxfrm(char *str1, const char *str2, size_t count);

  The strxfrm( ) function transforms the string pointed to by str2 
  so that it can be used by the strcmp ( ) function and puts 
  the result into the string pointed to by str1. 
  
  The following line transforms the first 10 characters of 
  the string pointed to by s2 and puts the result in the string 
  pointed to by s1.
  
  strxfrm(s1, s2, 10);
  
